content.description: Intriguing start leads to fun movement on the blunt arete.
content.location: Just to the right of Four Fingers, start with a left crimp and crystal for your right.

content.description: Interesting wave shaped boulder that looks like the head of a gorilla. A little cryptic at first, but once dialed, the climbing is quite fun.
content.location:
Facing the valley at the Easter Island boulders.

Start sitting on jugs on the "pedestal" and climb up using the right arete

content.description:
Steller traverse through a vain of bullet granite.

Crux comes soon after the start requiring a long shouldery between big edges
content.location:
In the middle of the Treasure Chest area, the boulder is hard to miss. Start on the very right side of the boulder, and traverse all the way left before going up the sloping lip.

Downclimb the slab on the backside

content.description:
Cruxy start leads to good movement and an exciting finish.

A little crumbly, but it still climbs really well.
content.location: Facing the road at the Easter Island boulders. Start on the right side of the boulder at chest high crimps. Climb up into the center of the boulder up to a sloping lip.

content.description:
Excellent problem on some of the better rock at the Phone Booth area.

An extended start goes at v6 by starting to the right on the flake, making tricky moves onto the edges of the stand-start
content.location: Located in the Good Stuff boulders, locate the scoop and start on edges at head height and move left through good crimps up to a fun deadpoint to a crystal at the top.

content.description: Fun hand crack offering solid jams, easy topout
content.protection: pads, rocks at base of the boulder
content.location: Facing the valley at the Easter Island area. Start standing and ascent the short crack

content.description:
Short problem with an interesting hold.

Good enough to warm up on, but Toe Thumb to the right is a better problem
content.location: Just to the right of Silverback, start on holds at waist height and climb up using the crack, or just skip it and go to the jug.

content.description:
Ascend the proud line straight up through a lie-back arete. Excellent warmup with an easy topout 15ft up

youtube.com/watch?v=Sv-bSiFâ€¦
content.location: Located at the Good Stuff area, this line climbs up the right side of the boulder

content.description: Just plain fun. This is a great boulder with several lines going up the blocky granite/quartz face
content.location: Just behind the Shark Fin boulder, start on  any of the great holds and climb up.
